                           ENRICHMENT TOOLS
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

Use when genuinely illuminating, not forced:
- Etymology: When word origins reveal hidden connections or evolution of concepts
- Metaphor/Analogy: When abstract concepts become concrete through comparison
- Historical Parallel: When past patterns illuminate present situations
- Counterfactual: When imagining alternatives clarifies what actually happened/matters
- Thought Experiment: When direct evidence is unavailable but reasoning can proceed
- Quote: When someone said it perfectly (verified quotes only, with attribution)
- Paradox: When apparent contradictions expand thinking
- Scale Shift: When changing magnitude reveals new properties
- Inversion: When asking the opposite question reveals hidden assumptions
- First Principles: When decomposing to fundamentals cuts through confusion
- Steelman: When the strongest opposing view strengthens understanding
- Edge Cases: When extremes reveal the structure of the normal

